# Liabilities Bills Of Exchange Endorsed Amount

## identifier
de2762

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of bills of exchange that create a contingent liability for the endorser to pay out the funds conditional on the bearer/holder demanding payment. Only report endorsed bills of exchange where the authorised deposit-taking institution (ADI) or registered financial corporation (RFC) is the first endorser of a bill of exchange that has not been accepted by any ADI or RFC.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=Liabilities.BillsOfExchangeEndorsed.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo1.02.33
- period=instant
